body_html:
Please pay attention to the issue template (https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/new) . Please provide all the information it asks.

In particular, it would be helpful to know more about the version of TensorFlow you're using. It seems the Android code is from an older version of TensorFlow (1.0 or prior? since tensorflow_inference_jni.cc was removed by version 1.1).

Anyway, from the error message it seems that perhaps the model file being used by your Android application (optimized_graph.pb) is different from the model you described earlier (frozen_graph.pb). It is possible that the graph in the Android asset does not have any node named output?

body:
Please pay attention to the issue template (https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/new) . Please provide all the information it asks.

In particular, it would be helpful to know more about the version of TensorFlow you're using. It seems the Android code is from an older version of TensorFlow (1.0 or prior? since `tensorflow_inference_jni.cc` was removed by version 1.1).

Anyway, from the error message it seems that perhaps the model file being used by your Android application (`optimized_graph.pb`) is different from the model you described earlier (`frozen_graph.pb`). It is possible that the graph in the Android asset does not have any node named `output`?
